.SH SAXON EDITION NOTES
.TP
.B Saxon 6.5.3
Open\-source, Mozilla Public Licence 1.0.  XSLT 1.0 processor.  Ships inside
the SilkPage toolchain at
.IR silkpage/core/share/lib/java/saxon\-6_5_3.jar .
The DocBook XSL chunker detects it via
.I element\-available('saxon:output')
(namespace
.IR http://icl.com/saxon )
and uses it to write multiple output files.
.TP
.B Saxon\-HE 9.2.0.2J
Open\-source, Mozilla Public Licence 2.0.  XSLT 2.0 / XPath 2.0 processor.
Ships inside the SilkPage toolchain at
.IR silkpage/core/share/lib/java/saxon9he.jar .
Cannot drive the DocBook XSL 1.x chunker (XTDE1480 \(em
.I xsl:result\-document
is not permitted inside a temporary\-tree context).  Used only for
the non\-chunked
.B make single
target.
.
.SH DOCBOOK TOOLCHAIN NOTES
The XML catalog at
.I silkpage/core/cfg/catalog\-resolved.xml
rewrites two URI patterns:
.TP
.I http://docbook.sourceforge.net/release/xsl/current/
Rewritten to the local DocBook XSL snapshot at
.IR silkpage/tools/docbook\-xsl/ .
.TP
.I http://silkpage.markupware.com/release/core/current/src/xsl/
Rewritten to the local SilkPage XSL directory at
.IR silkpage/core/src/xsl/ .
.PP
Both Saxon processors load the catalog via the Apache XML Commons Resolver
class
.I org.apache.xml.resolver.tools.CatalogResolver
configured with the system property
.BR \-Dxml.catalog.files=<PATH> .
.
